1
00:00:37,233 --> 00:00:38,233
Hey!

2
00:00:40,769 --> 00:00:41,862
You guys are too much...

3
00:00:41,887 --> 00:00:42,948
- What is this?
- What the?!

4
00:00:42,973 --> 00:00:44,782
You're going to give me a heart attack!

5
00:00:45,395 --> 00:00:46,395
Unbelievable.

6
00:00:47,140 --> 00:00:49,454
It's because, Dad,
you're just standing there like a statue.

7
00:00:49,507 --> 00:00:50,507
Yeah!

8
00:00:50,560 --> 00:00:52,787
Dad! It's our grand reopening today,

9
00:00:53,534 --> 00:00:55,888
but you're still rummaging
through stuff in a box.

10
00:00:56,662 --> 00:01:00,597
No, it's just that I was looking
at these awards of yours,

11
00:01:00,621 --> 00:01:04,556
and it feels so nostalgic, you know?

12
00:01:04,581 --> 00:01:06,864
Just think about it, Andres, Atasha—

13
00:01:07,819 --> 00:01:09,132
where we came from.

14
00:01:09,252 --> 00:01:10,292
And now,

15
00:01:11,428 --> 00:01:13,975
it's the grand reopening of our bake shop.

16
00:01:14,588 --> 00:01:15,806
- Isn't that amazing?
- It really is, Dad.

17
00:01:15,831 --> 00:01:18,203
And we've been through a lot, right?

18
00:01:18,307 --> 00:01:21,120
We started from the bottom,
now we’re here!

19
00:01:22,329 --> 00:01:24,029
That’s true, that’s true.
But you know,

20
00:01:24,417 --> 00:01:28,817
these awards make me
so proud of you both. Really.

21
00:01:28,852 --> 00:01:31,979
But you know what else
makes me proud?

22
00:01:32,079 --> 00:01:33,225
Of course, I know!

23
00:01:34,302 --> 00:01:37,096
This trophy of mine from
the basketball championship!

24
00:01:37,817 --> 00:01:39,117
We got first place with that!

25
00:01:39,715 --> 00:01:40,748
Or...

26
00:01:40,808 --> 00:01:45,400
I think my gold medal
from high school is better

27
00:01:45,425 --> 00:01:48,217
because I was first honors with that!

28
00:01:48,242 --> 00:01:50,001
Or... hold on... or...

29
00:01:50,026 --> 00:01:51,026
this

30
00:01:52,268 --> 00:01:55,708
certificate of participation
from the poster-making contest!

31
00:01:55,733 --> 00:01:56,733
Poster-making?!

32
00:01:57,311 --> 00:01:58,311
First—

33
00:01:58,933 --> 00:02:00,942
- First place?
- I didn’t win, but...

34
00:02:01,845 --> 00:02:03,359
it was my first time joining a contest!

35
00:02:03,563 --> 00:02:04,650
Oh, that works,

36
00:02:04,709 --> 00:02:05,783
but, sorry, Andres,

37
00:02:06,605 --> 00:02:10,866
my "Most Punctual" ribbon
from kindergarten is better

38
00:02:11,138 --> 00:02:14,871
because I was always
the first to arrive at school!

39
00:02:14,896 --> 00:02:17,330
Alright, alright. You know,
all of that makes me proud.

40
00:02:17,485 --> 00:02:19,585
I’m really proud of both of you,
Andres and Atasha.

41
00:02:19,629 --> 00:02:24,144
But do you know what
I’m really focusing on here?

42
00:02:25,130 --> 00:02:26,130
This.

43
00:02:27,018 --> 00:02:28,018
Oh...

44
00:02:28,149 --> 00:02:29,149
Because this,

45
00:02:29,848 --> 00:02:31,688
we all worked hard for it, didn’t we?

46
00:02:31,738 --> 00:02:38,324
This is the first review of our very
first Bake Haus of U bake shop.

47
00:02:38,590 --> 00:02:40,885
Oh, yeah, I remember.

48
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:45,493
And I’m sure Kuya Andres
hasn’t forgotten that either!

49
00:02:45,639 --> 00:02:46,906
I don’t remember, actually.

50
00:02:46,961 --> 00:02:48,808
Oh, really?

51
00:02:48,833 --> 00:02:50,954
You really want us
to remind you, huh?

52
00:02:51,248 --> 00:02:54,165
The time when Mom made that big cake?

53
00:03:56,537 --> 00:03:58,424
It was beautiful!

54
00:03:59,452 --> 00:04:01,425
Ate Cha did an amazing job!

55
00:04:01,450 --> 00:04:03,149
- Right? It was incredible, isn’t it?
- Yes.

56
00:04:03,174 --> 00:04:04,744
That’s how it is when
it’s the "Pers family!"

57
00:04:04,769 --> 00:04:05,769
Exactly!

58
00:04:06,092 --> 00:04:08,039
And here you are,
bloodsucker to Ate Cha!

59
00:04:08,064 --> 00:04:10,334
I’m not! Just saying it as it is!

60
00:04:10,359 --> 00:04:11,900
- Here, help me, please.
- Alright.

61
00:04:11,937 --> 00:04:14,418
- Okay, okay, okay! Wait a second.
- Here, deliver this, okay?

62
00:04:14,443 --> 00:04:16,724
Wait, wait, take this too. Alright!

63
00:04:16,749 --> 00:04:19,228
It’s mixed with love and passion!

64
00:04:19,253 --> 00:04:21,694
Yes, I really made it
with love and passion,

65
00:04:21,718 --> 00:04:24,158
but you need to handleit carefully, okay?

66
00:04:24,316 --> 00:04:25,369
Is the delivery nearby?

67
00:04:25,394 --> 00:04:26,915
- Yes, it’s just close by.
- So we’ll deliver it manually?

68
00:04:26,940 --> 00:04:29,719
Yes, just like that.
And then just come back right away!

69
00:04:29,761 --> 00:04:31,134
- Alright.
- We can handle this.

70
00:04:31,159 --> 00:04:32,159
You got this! You can do it!

71
00:04:32,192 --> 00:04:34,623
- Alright, come on, come on.
- Careful, careful!

72
00:04:34,681 --> 00:04:37,669
Alright, take care, okay?

73
00:04:37,781 --> 00:04:39,034
- Alright, be careful!
- Oh no, this is special.

74
00:04:39,059 --> 00:04:42,953
- Hey, take care of that! Careful, careful!
- Hey!

75
00:04:43,668 --> 00:04:44,668
Careful!

76
00:04:45,316 --> 00:04:46,316
- Oh!
- Hey!

77
00:04:46,404 --> 00:04:47,691
Please! Careful!

78
00:04:48,875 --> 00:04:50,356
- Oh!
- No, no!

79
00:04:50,380 --> 00:04:51,766
Be careful with that! Oh no!

80
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,185
Help, Iskineport!

81
00:04:58,348 --> 00:04:59,781
Help, Iskineport!

82
00:04:59,918 --> 00:05:02,938
Did you see those two?
Gosh, that Iskineport!

83
00:05:02,963 --> 00:05:04,599
Oh, my heart, I can’t take it!

84
00:05:05,516 --> 00:05:07,316
Relax, don’t stress yourself!

85
00:05:07,341 --> 00:05:10,929
It’s just that I made that cake with love.
I was even sweating over it.

86
00:05:10,954 --> 00:05:14,674
Exactly. It’s okay now.
See, it’s safe now.

87
00:05:14,912 --> 00:05:16,125
Just remember this, okay?

88
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:20,093
I don’t want to hear any complaints
from the customers, alright?

89
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:23,161
- Got it.
- Remember, the customer is always right.

90
00:05:23,227 --> 00:05:24,227
- That’s right!
- Dad!

91
00:05:24,327 --> 00:05:25,840
That saying is so outdated.

92
00:05:26,226 --> 00:05:27,726
Customers aren’t always perfect

93
00:05:28,113 --> 00:05:29,113
Also, Dad,

94
00:05:29,138 --> 00:05:32,771
the full saying is actually
“The customer is always right...

95
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,513
in terms of taste.”

96
00:05:35,186 --> 00:05:37,966
Meaning, if they like hopia better,

97
00:05:38,507 --> 00:05:41,260
even if we think crinkles are tastier,

98
00:05:41,592 --> 00:05:46,272
we let them buy hopia
or whatever they prefer.

99
00:05:46,297 --> 00:05:50,848
But it doesn’t include
tolerating bad attitudes.

100
00:05:51,072 --> 00:05:52,212
Alright. Fine, okay.

101
00:05:52,237 --> 00:05:54,454
You said a lot there.

102
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:56,037
Let’s just say this
instead to make it clear:

103
00:05:56,061 --> 00:05:59,688
The customer
is always "Pers."

104
00:06:00,154 --> 00:06:02,747
- Oooohhh...
- Meaning, first priority.

105
00:06:02,881 --> 00:06:04,906
- That sounds good!
- Got it?

106
00:06:04,944 --> 00:06:06,224
- Got it!
- Yes, Dad!

107
00:06:06,533 --> 00:06:07,533
Okay.

108
00:06:07,558 --> 00:06:09,565
Will we hit our sales quota today?

109
00:06:09,764 --> 00:06:11,387
- Yes, Dad!
- Yes, we will.

110
00:06:11,412 --> 00:06:12,913
Okay. Is your Daddy handsome?

111
00:06:14,154 --> 00:06:15,708
I’ll put the pandesal—

112
00:06:15,956 --> 00:06:17,083
Andres, customer!

113
00:06:17,108 --> 00:06:18,973
Looks like there’s a
customer at the counter.

114
00:06:21,661 --> 00:06:22,921
- Nobody answered.
- Me!

115
00:06:23,023 --> 00:06:25,166
You’re handsome, my love!

116
00:06:25,191 --> 00:06:28,350
Thank you, my love, thank you, my love.
Oh, thank you!

117
00:06:28,375 --> 00:06:31,734
Sales are picking up here, huh?
Do your work properly, okay?

118
00:06:32,232 --> 00:06:34,202
And you, stop those
vices of yours, alright?!

119
00:06:34,388 --> 00:06:36,002
You’re close to breaking down.

120
00:06:36,027 --> 00:06:38,350
My goodness, it looks like
you’ll need dextrose next time!

121
00:06:41,092 --> 00:06:42,759
- Mariposa! Mariposa!
- What is it?

122
00:06:42,784 --> 00:06:43,473
Wait a second.

123
00:06:43,498 --> 00:06:44,577
- It’s Iskineport!
- What’s that?

124
00:06:44,945 --> 00:06:47,805
- What’s that?
- I have no idea.

125
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:48,902
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

126
00:06:48,927 --> 00:06:50,714
- Oh? Oh, no!
- Oh, my!

127
00:06:50,752 --> 00:06:51,752
Careful with it!

128
00:06:53,029 --> 00:06:55,196
- Iskineport, what’s that?
- What’s that?

129
00:06:55,553 --> 00:06:56,807
Uh, slippers!

130
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:58,020
Obviously—cake!

131
00:06:58,045 --> 00:06:59,124
For who?

132
00:06:59,149 --> 00:07:02,041
Not for you! So stop asking,
we’re in a hurry!

133
00:07:02,066 --> 00:07:04,142
- So grumpy!
- Very grumpy!

134
00:07:04,220 --> 00:07:05,220
Oops, oops, oops!

135
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:07,874
A rushing grumpy person!

136
00:07:07,899 --> 00:07:08,978
Get out of the way!

137
00:07:09,009 --> 00:07:11,264
- Excuse me!
- They’re rushing, bestie!

138
00:07:11,289 --> 00:07:12,289
Move aside!

139
00:07:12,314 --> 00:07:13,314
Wait a minute!

140
00:07:13,862 --> 00:07:14,862
Hold on!

141
00:07:14,887 --> 00:07:16,415
- Later!
- You dropped a coin!

142
00:07:16,429 --> 00:07:17,749
Oh, Boss Beauty!

143
00:07:17,773 --> 00:07:19,679
Oh no, looks like you
stepped on something gross!

144
00:07:19,704 --> 00:07:21,947
Oh my god, poop?!

145
00:07:22,389 --> 00:07:24,083
- We’re in a hurry!
- Oh, oh! Oh my!

146
00:07:24,156 --> 00:07:26,236
Alright, alright, go ahead, irritate us!

147
00:07:26,959 --> 00:07:29,019
We’ll come back for you!
After this, we’ll deal with you!

148
00:07:29,414 --> 00:07:30,468
Some of those don’t even have covers!

149
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:32,160
Wait for us until we get back!

150
00:07:32,733 --> 00:07:34,086
We’re coming back for you!

151
00:07:34,323 --> 00:07:36,617
Go ahead! We’re neighbors anyway!

152
00:07:37,763 --> 00:07:38,763
Exactly!

153
00:07:39,133 --> 00:07:40,206
Here are your drinks.

154
00:07:46,733 --> 00:07:47,967
Thank you, thanks, alright!

155
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:49,320
Thank you!

156
00:07:49,677 --> 00:07:50,677
What about you?

157
00:07:52,825 --> 00:07:53,825
BFF!

158
00:07:54,743 --> 00:07:55,743
- BFF!
- The place is jam-packed, huh?

159
00:07:56,824 --> 00:08:00,204
By the way, I heard that
when you knead dough,

160
00:08:00,696 --> 00:08:02,409
you don’t wash your hands?

161
00:08:02,660 --> 00:08:04,253
Huh? Is that true?

162
00:08:04,371 --> 00:08:06,268
- Alright, I won’t buy then.
- No, no...

163
00:08:06,293 --> 00:08:07,293
- Is that true?
- Wait. Hold on!

164
00:08:07,323 --> 00:08:08,770
Wait. Hold on!

165
00:08:08,795 --> 00:08:09,909
Do you wash your hands?

166
00:08:09,934 --> 00:08:10,934
That’s not true!

167
00:08:11,004 --> 00:08:12,184
BFF! That’s not true!

168
00:08:12,342 --> 00:08:13,435
Huh? Is it really not true?

169
00:08:13,715 --> 00:08:15,423
What’s wrong with you,
look, the customers left!

170
00:08:15,448 --> 00:08:18,151
No, I just heard that!
Good thing you clarified it!

171
00:08:18,180 --> 00:08:19,946
Oh, so you do wash your hands!

172
00:08:19,971 --> 00:08:22,206
Please stop with the crab mentality!

173
00:08:23,258 --> 00:08:24,972
I just heard it.

174
00:08:25,222 --> 00:08:26,222
I mean, you should—

175
00:08:26,247 --> 00:08:27,943
Well, the customer left,
but it’s okay... Oh, eh...

176
00:08:27,968 --> 00:08:29,097
There’s no one left, huh.

177
00:08:29,363 --> 00:08:31,350
No, look. Someone’s coming.

178
00:08:31,802 --> 00:08:34,716
Oh, there, it’s our customer.

179
00:08:35,475 --> 00:08:36,475
- Hey!
- Oh,

180
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:38,121
what happened to you?
What’s going on with you, why?

181
00:08:38,824 --> 00:08:39,824
Your hands are wet, why?

182
00:08:39,849 --> 00:08:41,287
- What happened to you?
- Don’t you know who that is?!

183
00:08:41,866 --> 00:08:43,526
What’s wrong with you,
don’t you know anything?!

184
00:08:43,570 --> 00:08:44,710
Why are you trembling?

185
00:08:44,735 --> 00:08:46,670
That’s someone famous,
someone famous!

186
00:08:46,878 --> 00:08:49,158
That’s Goldie Azucarera!

187
00:08:49,522 --> 00:08:50,982
You know her? A food critic!

188
00:08:51,730 --> 00:08:53,410
When she writes her reviews,

189
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:57,559
businesses shut down because of her!

190
00:08:57,650 --> 00:08:59,510
She’s a terror, a terror!

191
00:09:00,181 --> 00:09:03,107
Dad, she looks like my
terror Math teacher back then!

192
00:09:03,344 --> 00:09:04,778
The one who failed me.

193
00:09:04,804 --> 00:09:05,888
- She failed you?
- Yes!

194
00:09:05,913 --> 00:09:07,375
So many people failed you back then!

195
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:08,414
- Oh.
- What’s wrong with you!

196
00:09:08,453 --> 00:09:10,786
Unbelievable.
I still have trauma from that!

197
00:09:10,811 --> 00:09:12,468
No, really, just stay there!
Wait a second!

198
00:09:12,493 --> 00:09:16,696
No, no... she’s probably not
here for our bake house, right?

199
00:09:16,909 --> 00:09:18,483
Ah, probably not. You’re just a bakery.

200
00:09:18,702 --> 00:09:20,735
I think she only goes
for the big-time places.

201
00:09:28,801 --> 00:09:29,801
Yes, Ma’am?

202
00:09:29,948 --> 00:09:31,208
One ensaymada, please!

203
00:09:34,277 --> 00:09:35,684
Ah, one ensaymada!

204
00:09:37,083 --> 00:09:38,083
Alright!

205
00:09:40,165 --> 00:09:41,165
Ensaymada.

206
00:09:41,717 --> 00:09:42,717
One.

207
00:09:42,742 --> 00:09:43,742
- One.
- Yes, Ma’am!

208
00:09:59,610 --> 00:10:00,983
Oh, good day!

209
00:10:01,172 --> 00:10:02,252
Come in, come in.

210
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,907
Oh, is this for Kurt Rosal?

211
00:10:04,014 --> 00:10:05,014
Yes, it is.

212
00:10:05,039 --> 00:10:08,299
Alright, please place the cake there.

213
00:10:12,260 --> 00:10:13,639
- Please close the door.
- Oh, sorry!

214
00:10:14,394 --> 00:10:17,334
There’s a children’s party here!
Wow, so fun!

215
00:10:17,408 --> 00:10:19,549
- There’s so much food!
- Where’s the child, I wonder?

216
00:10:20,846 --> 00:10:22,193
Why are you looking for the child?

217
00:10:22,774 --> 00:10:25,307
The dad is here—that’s the one who
will pay, and that’s what’s important!

218
00:10:25,338 --> 00:10:26,711
Oh, okay!

219
00:10:26,736 --> 00:10:28,331
Sir, here’s your bill.

220
00:10:28,775 --> 00:10:29,775
Yes.

221
00:10:32,199 --> 00:10:33,199
There you go.

222
00:10:33,402 --> 00:10:36,056
Let me just get my wallet
so I can pay you.

223
00:10:37,163 --> 00:10:38,196
Why don’t you eat, meanwhile.

224
00:10:38,325 --> 00:10:41,132
Oh, we really need to go
because we still have to—

225
00:10:42,191 --> 00:10:44,284
We have nothing else to do! Huh?

226
00:10:44,466 --> 00:10:45,872
We don’t have anything to do, right?

227
00:10:46,107 --> 00:10:49,807
Alright, go ahead and get your wallet.
Should we eat?

228
00:10:49,832 --> 00:10:50,832
Sure, go ahead.

229
00:10:51,037 --> 00:10:52,037
Stop fighting it!

230
00:10:52,055 --> 00:10:53,055
Okay.

231
00:10:54,873 --> 00:10:55,873
You’re so tense!

232
00:10:56,931 --> 00:10:58,244
What are we going to do?
We have nothing to do!

233
00:10:58,269 --> 00:10:59,521
But we really need to leave!

234
00:10:59,546 --> 00:11:01,945
Why leave? The dad is treating us!

235
00:11:02,098 --> 00:11:03,985
- Oh yeah, the food’s great!
- Go ahead, eat!

236
00:11:04,010 --> 00:11:05,010
- Wow...
- What about Kuya Aga?!

237
00:11:05,013 --> 00:11:06,013
…bopis?!

238
00:11:06,099 --> 00:11:07,099
Blood stew?!

239
00:11:07,276 --> 00:11:09,116
All innards—my favorite!

240
00:11:09,141 --> 00:11:10,141
Oh my...

241
00:11:11,871 --> 00:11:13,201
- My love?
- Huh, what?

242
00:11:13,388 --> 00:11:14,388
- Huh, what? My love?
- Yeah?

243
00:11:14,446 --> 00:11:15,446
Is the ensaymada ready?

244
00:11:15,469 --> 00:11:17,403
Ah… about that...

245
00:11:17,729 --> 00:11:19,456
- What’s wrong? Why?
- Because, um…

246
00:11:19,782 --> 00:11:20,915
I broke the oven?

247
00:11:21,301 --> 00:11:23,834
Because it’s the first time we’ve
had such a large cake order!

248
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:28,317
It seems like... I overused the oven!

249
00:11:28,415 --> 00:11:29,415
And now it’s broken!

250
00:11:29,419 --> 00:11:30,799
What?! The oven’s broken?!

251
00:11:31,196 --> 00:11:32,865
- Yes.
- The oven’s broken?!

252
00:11:32,890 --> 00:11:36,035
Aren’t you overreacting a bit, my love?

253
00:11:36,487 --> 00:11:39,867
My love, exaggerated—my love...
do you know Goldie Azucarera?

254
00:11:40,086 --> 00:11:43,060
The food critic everyone’s afraid of?

255
00:11:43,172 --> 00:11:44,950
- Mm-hmm.
- You know,

256
00:11:45,043 --> 00:11:52,380
I used to get so nervous at the
thought of her reviewing our bakery.

257
00:11:52,405 --> 00:11:53,985
It gave me chills!

258
00:11:55,103 --> 00:11:56,103
- Okay…
- Oh?

259
00:11:56,128 --> 00:11:57,482
- Are you done? Okay.
- Yeah, done.

260
00:11:57,541 --> 00:11:59,441
So, Goldie,
the one you were talking about...

261
00:11:59,466 --> 00:12:01,525
- Mmm?
- She’s here. Outside.

262
00:12:01,550 --> 00:12:03,203
- What?!
- She ordered ensaymada!

263
00:12:03,228 --> 00:12:05,475
What are we going to do, my love?
What are we going to do?!

264
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:07,487
My love, what are we going to do?!

265
00:12:07,512 --> 00:12:09,521
See, look at your reaction!
Look at your reaction!

266
00:12:09,546 --> 00:12:10,703
What are we going to do?!

267
00:12:10,741 --> 00:12:12,848
That’s what I’m saying—who’s
going to fix our oven?!

268
00:12:12,873 --> 00:12:16,376
- I don’t know, what are we going to do?!
- Where are Iskineport and Chard?!

269
00:12:16,707 --> 00:12:19,940
Shhh! What’s going on here?
Why are you being so loud?

270
00:12:20,274 --> 00:12:23,641
Hey, I can hear you from outside!

271
00:12:23,666 --> 00:12:24,696
The oven’s broken?!

272
00:12:24,721 --> 00:12:26,087
- The oven’s broken, Lola Maxi!
- Yes, it’s broken!

273
00:12:26,141 --> 00:12:27,315
Do you know how to fix an oven?!

274
00:12:27,432 --> 00:12:28,912
Of course!

275
00:12:28,937 --> 00:12:31,758
Your Lolo Roman taught
me how to fix these things.

276
00:12:31,783 --> 00:12:32,838
Oh, thank goodness!

277
00:12:33,158 --> 00:12:35,004
- Okay, okay, okay, okay, okay!
- Okay, okay, okay, okay!

278
00:12:35,029 --> 00:12:36,277
Help Lola Maxi!

279
00:12:36,309 --> 00:12:37,682
- I’ll take over.
- Okay, okay, okay, okay.

280
00:12:38,162 --> 00:12:39,162
Here we go!

281
00:12:39,316 --> 00:12:40,316
- Lola Maxi.
- Here we go!

282
00:12:41,086 --> 00:12:43,146
- See? What did I tell you?!
- See, told you!

283
00:12:43,171 --> 00:12:44,171
It’s fine now?

284
00:12:44,449 --> 00:12:46,312
- It’s nothing, no problem!
- Oh, be careful, it’s hot.

285
00:12:46,337 --> 00:12:47,651
Be careful!

286
00:12:47,688 --> 00:12:48,688
- There.
- Here we go.

287
00:12:48,713 --> 00:12:50,079
Here it is, here it is!

288
00:12:50,104 --> 00:12:51,104
Spot me.

289
00:12:51,129 --> 00:12:52,201
Alright, alright. Careful,
let me help you, Lola Maxi.

290
00:12:52,314 --> 00:12:53,769
- Careful, Lola Maxi!
- Careful, please! Oh, my goodness!

291
00:12:53,803 --> 00:12:55,405
- Ma’am Goldie –
- Miss Goldie!

292
00:12:55,824 --> 00:12:56,878
Oh, sorry,

293
00:12:56,928 --> 00:12:57,928
but…

294
00:12:57,953 --> 00:13:00,513
there’s just a slight technical
difficulty with your order.

295
00:13:00,927 --> 00:13:01,927
Please have some coffee
while you wait.

296
00:13:04,601 --> 00:13:06,741
Uh, um… Ma’am Goldie…

297
00:13:06,968 --> 00:13:07,968
Miss Goldie!

298
00:13:07,993 --> 00:13:09,766
Miss Goldie, sorry.

299
00:13:09,886 --> 00:13:10,886
Uh...

300
00:13:11,249 --> 00:13:13,216
what exactly is your purpose here?

301
00:13:13,701 --> 00:13:18,761
I’m here to write a review for
the best ensaymada in the metro!

302
00:13:19,275 --> 00:13:22,155
I’m tired of the usual bakeshops!

303
00:13:22,950 --> 00:13:26,911
That’s why I’m scouting
for the best ensaymada.

304
00:13:27,182 --> 00:13:30,189
My amiga recommended your place.

305
00:13:30,812 --> 00:13:32,932
If she’s right, then you’re lucky!

306
00:13:33,562 --> 00:13:34,562
If not,

307
00:13:34,839 --> 00:13:36,978
maybe you should consider
turning this space

308
00:13:37,002 --> 00:13:39,141
into a water station or a thrift shop.

309
00:13:39,834 --> 00:13:40,834
Any other questions?

310
00:13:41,022 --> 00:13:42,649
Ah, none, ma’am. None at all.

311
00:13:45,186 --> 00:13:47,019
Oh no!

312
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:50,200
The ensaymada’s still not ready?

313
00:13:50,606 --> 00:13:51,606
This is embarrassing!

314
00:13:51,794 --> 00:13:53,927
The customer is waiting!

315
00:13:54,851 --> 00:13:56,831
I’m willing to wait—if it’s worth it!

316
00:13:57,076 --> 00:14:00,515
Oh no, she’s waiting!
It’ll take a while!

317
00:14:00,608 --> 00:14:02,508
Ah, what are you doing with my bag?

318
00:14:03,127 --> 00:14:04,851
Your bag?
Oh, nothing!

319
00:14:05,062 --> 00:14:08,525
I was just thinking of inviting you
over to my bakery instead!

320
00:14:09,107 --> 00:14:11,294
We also have special ensaymada.

321
00:14:11,591 --> 00:14:15,064
I promise, once you taste it,
you won’t come back here!

322
00:14:16,341 --> 00:14:17,708
Fine, I’m bored.

323
00:14:28,653 --> 00:14:29,966
- Hi, Sir!
- Hi!

324
00:14:30,403 --> 00:14:31,403
Did you enjoy the food?

325
00:14:31,428 --> 00:14:32,921
- Yes!
- Thank you!

326
00:14:32,958 --> 00:14:36,544
We’re stuffed, we ate so much! Look!

327
00:14:36,711 --> 00:14:37,711
Have more!

328
00:14:37,736 --> 00:14:41,350
Oh, we’re full, but…
can we pack some to go?

329
00:14:41,426 --> 00:14:43,373
Sure, pack what you want!

330
00:14:43,446 --> 00:14:46,953
- Yes! Thank you!
- Yes! Yes! Yes!

331
00:14:52,310 --> 00:14:54,284
Get the cabbage—it’s great for cooking!

332
00:14:56,577 --> 00:14:58,741
Cabbage is so expensive right now!

333
00:14:58,804 --> 00:14:59,864
Vegetables are so pricey!

334
00:14:59,888 --> 00:15:01,174
- Thank you, sir!
- Yes, sir!

335
00:15:01,223 --> 00:15:03,636
I really enjoyed this!

336
00:15:03,863 --> 00:15:07,643
But we need to go now
to deliver this to Kuya Aga!

337
00:15:07,861 --> 00:15:08,975
Wait!

338
00:15:09,899 --> 00:15:11,875
Why are you in such a rush?
We don’t have anything scheduled!

339
00:15:11,900 --> 00:15:13,502
They told us to come back soon!

340
00:15:13,602 --> 00:15:14,602
Nothing!

341
00:15:14,699 --> 00:15:16,846
There’s nothing to do!

342
00:15:16,871 --> 00:15:20,300
Why don’t you sing for
the birthday celebrant?

343
00:15:20,477 --> 00:15:27,113
Oh, but… there are no guests yet, and
the birthday boy, Kurt, isn’t here yet?

344
00:15:27,145 --> 00:15:28,963
- Yeah.
- I’m Kurt!

345
00:15:28,991 --> 00:15:30,324
- You’re Kurt?
- Yes!

346
00:15:30,355 --> 00:15:31,476
He’s the birthday celebrant!

347
00:15:32,141 --> 00:15:33,687
Sing for me!

348
00:15:33,998 --> 00:15:37,453
Oh, we don’t know how to sing!
We were just here to eat—

349
00:15:37,478 --> 00:15:38,781
You don’t know how?!

350
00:15:40,365 --> 00:15:41,365
Ah!

351
00:15:43,373 --> 00:15:48,600
- Happy birthday to you!
- Happy birthday to you...

352
00:15:48,625 --> 00:15:50,191
Dance for me!

353
00:15:50,404 --> 00:15:52,984
Happy birthday to you!

354
00:15:53,614 --> 00:15:56,468
Happy birthday to you!

355
00:16:00,931 --> 00:16:01,931
Wait…

356
00:16:02,264 --> 00:16:04,597
we didn’t make this.

357
00:16:05,290 --> 00:16:07,296
We bought it from Bread Ribbon.

358
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:09,567
Isn’t that unfair?

359
00:16:10,146 --> 00:16:11,146
Yeah, and?

360
00:16:11,486 --> 00:16:12,759
Life is unfair!

361
00:16:13,321 --> 00:16:15,847
It’s just like when you find “the one,”

362
00:16:16,276 --> 00:16:22,767
and then your friend steals
them from you!

363
00:16:24,260 --> 00:16:26,034
Wow, Tso K, your feelings run deep.

364
00:16:26,631 --> 00:16:27,657
Like a well!

365
00:16:28,046 --> 00:16:29,894
Oh, never mind.
Don’t worry about it.

366
00:16:29,919 --> 00:16:34,441
Once we get a good review
from her, we’ll win big!

367
00:16:34,686 --> 00:16:36,386
The bakery will be famous!

368
00:16:36,463 --> 00:16:37,470
And not just that,

369
00:16:37,807 --> 00:16:42,637
Cha will come crawling
back to me, begging,

370
00:16:43,081 --> 00:16:45,954
“Take me back! Please take me back!”

371
00:16:47,533 --> 00:16:49,156
- Question.
- What?

372
00:16:49,181 --> 00:16:52,227
How can someone come back to you
if they were never yours to begin with?

373
00:16:53,378 --> 00:16:54,378
Another question.

374
00:16:54,804 --> 00:16:55,978
Why do you talk so much?

375
00:16:56,484 --> 00:16:57,671
You keep running your mouth!

376
00:16:57,696 --> 00:17:02,223
Just go! Gosh, if it weren’t for
the customers here, I’d really—ugh!

377
00:17:02,248 --> 00:17:03,248
Fine, I’ll do it myself.

378
00:17:04,117 --> 00:17:05,117
Really!

379
00:17:07,887 --> 00:17:08,887
Here it is.

380
00:17:12,681 --> 00:17:13,681
It’s hot.

381
00:17:14,978 --> 00:17:17,124
Are you sure about this ensaymada?

382
00:17:17,425 --> 00:17:19,646
- Of course!
- My taste buds are extremely sharp!

383
00:17:20,407 --> 00:17:21,967
Super sure.

384
00:17:23,153 --> 00:17:25,260
Tada!

385
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:28,920
Huh?

386
00:17:28,945 --> 00:17:29,945
This is ensaymada?

387
00:17:30,145 --> 00:17:31,145
Yes!

388
00:17:32,192 --> 00:17:33,538
You might not know this,

389
00:17:33,562 --> 00:17:37,838
but a lot of celebrities want
to endorse my ensaymada.

390
00:17:38,251 --> 00:17:39,991
I just keep turning them down.

391
00:17:40,952 --> 00:17:42,172
- Celebrities?
- Yes.

392
00:17:42,839 --> 00:17:43,839
Like who?

393
00:17:44,419 --> 00:17:47,313
Oh, like Sylvester Stallone!

394
00:17:47,338 --> 00:17:48,691
- Wow!
- Yeah, he loves it!

395
00:17:49,037 --> 00:17:51,330
- And Julia Roberts, too!
- Really, now?

396
00:17:51,443 --> 00:17:54,182
And Tiger Woods—this
is his breakfast staple!

397
00:17:54,207 --> 00:17:55,207
Let me try!

398
00:17:58,438 --> 00:17:59,438
Mmm!

399
00:18:02,297 --> 00:18:03,297
Delicious!

400
00:18:04,690 --> 00:18:05,690
Flavorful!

401
00:18:06,369 --> 00:18:08,626
Mmm, such a great texture too!

402
00:18:09,560 --> 00:18:10,560
See? I told you!

403
00:18:10,585 --> 00:18:11,938
You didn’t believe me!

404
00:18:12,230 --> 00:18:13,383
And factory-made!

405
00:18:13,994 --> 00:18:15,487
You think you can fool me?

406
00:18:15,808 --> 00:18:18,215
I already told you,
I have a sharp sense of taste!

407
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:19,937
Wha—wha—

408
00:18:19,962 --> 00:18:20,962
You know what?

409
00:18:21,091 --> 00:18:23,051
You don’t deserve a review!

410
00:18:23,246 --> 00:18:24,246
This is terrible!

411
00:18:24,271 --> 00:18:26,966
How could you?
You just wasted my pen’s ink!

412
00:18:27,005 --> 00:18:29,312
No—Miss Goldie, please don’t be like that!
Don’t be like that!

413
00:18:29,337 --> 00:18:30,349
You don’t deserve—

414
00:18:30,374 --> 00:18:31,694
Please forgive me! Hold on!

415
00:18:31,719 --> 00:18:34,748
Don’t shut down my bakery!
I’ll do anything!

416
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:36,286
You—kneel too!
Why am I the only one kneeling?

417
00:18:36,318 --> 00:18:37,318
Come on, help me out here!

418
00:18:37,437 --> 00:18:41,401
I’m sorry! We’ll do whatever you say,
just tell us!

419
00:18:41,426 --> 00:18:42,625
Boss Goldie, please forgive us!

420
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:44,094
Go on, beg!

421
00:18:44,154 --> 00:18:46,087
This is making me nervous, Iskineport!

422
00:18:47,632 --> 00:18:48,632
Hey!

423
00:18:49,132 --> 00:18:51,285
That person seems like a serial killer!

424
00:18:51,351 --> 00:18:54,438
What if they’re just fattening us up
and then planning to kill us?

425
00:18:54,463 --> 00:18:56,231
I feel like I’ve seen
this in a movie before!

426
00:18:56,256 --> 00:18:57,256
Don’t be scared!

427
00:18:57,264 --> 00:18:59,482
I’ve got your back!

428
00:18:59,507 --> 00:19:01,042
I’m with you—why are you scared?

429
00:19:01,067 --> 00:19:02,746
- Alright, alright. I’ll trust you.
- Stay steady!

430
00:19:02,771 --> 00:19:03,871
Where is he? Oh, there he is.

431
00:19:04,257 --> 00:19:05,563
- Stay calm.
- Is he here? Is he coming?

432
00:19:05,588 --> 00:19:06,588
Relax, relax.

433
00:19:07,294 --> 00:19:09,167
Uh, Sir Kurt,

434
00:19:10,681 --> 00:19:12,874
someone called me—it’s an emergency.

435
00:19:13,514 --> 00:19:15,480
They said we’re needed at our place.

436
00:19:15,511 --> 00:19:16,511
So we’re leaving now, okay?

437
00:19:16,573 --> 00:19:17,573
Mmm-mmm, I’ll come with you.

438
00:19:19,821 --> 00:19:20,821
Why, Sir?

439
00:19:21,724 --> 00:19:26,173
- Uh, Sir Kurt, why did you lock the door?
- Yeah, why?

440
00:19:26,283 --> 00:19:29,335
What are you talking about—someone
called you about an emergency?

441
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:33,278
- Yes.
- I saw your phone earlier—it’s dead!

442
00:19:34,148 --> 00:19:36,281
- Are you lying to me?
- How does he know?

443
00:19:36,334 --> 00:19:38,134
Oh, a charger.

444
00:19:38,159 --> 00:19:39,713
- Thanks for the charger.
- Charge it first.

445
00:19:39,738 --> 00:19:40,738
Okay.

446
00:19:40,763 --> 00:19:42,363
Maybe there was a ghost earlier?

447
00:19:42,450 --> 00:19:44,283
Hey, it’s already afternoon!

448
00:19:44,747 --> 00:19:46,194
Time flies so fast!

449
00:19:46,219 --> 00:19:47,219
It’s time!

450
00:19:47,232 --> 00:19:49,139
Oh, time to go home!

451
00:19:49,423 --> 00:19:51,183
- No!
- Ouch! Ow!

452
00:19:51,621 --> 00:19:52,714
What do you mean,
“time to go home”?

453
00:19:52,767 --> 00:19:53,780
Don’t go home just yet…

454
00:19:53,805 --> 00:19:55,366
What I meant was—

455
00:19:55,488 --> 00:19:58,354
it’s time for entertainment!

456
00:19:58,643 --> 00:20:04,279
You know, like at birthday parties
where there’s singing, dancing, and clowns!

457
00:20:04,419 --> 00:20:05,419
No!

458
00:20:06,285 --> 00:20:08,412
We’re not going to follow what you want!

459
00:20:08,740 --> 00:20:11,466
You even slammed my friend
into the wall earlier!

460
00:20:11,691 --> 00:20:15,224
You’ve been bossing us around all day!
You’re out of line!

461
00:20:15,249 --> 00:20:16,249
Right, Iskineport!

462
00:20:16,611 --> 00:20:17,611
Oh, really now?

463
00:20:19,892 --> 00:20:20,892
Cut!

464
00:20:21,079 --> 00:20:23,279
That’s my performance.

465
00:20:23,304 --> 00:20:25,304
He can do it too.
Go ahead, show them.

466
00:20:25,329 --> 00:20:27,329
Perform?
Ahh, Iskineport!

467
00:20:27,812 --> 00:20:29,906
I know magic!
I can do magic tricks!

468
00:20:30,007 --> 00:20:31,951
I can amaze you with my talent!
Here it is—

469
00:20:32,004 --> 00:20:33,857
close your eyes, close your eyes!

470
00:20:33,882 --> 00:20:37,609
When I count to three,
we’ll disappear like magic! You like that?

471
00:20:38,349 --> 00:20:39,349
I don’t.

472
00:20:39,938 --> 00:20:43,265
- I want to be able to keep an eye on you.
- He doesn’t want it.

473
00:20:44,423 --> 00:20:46,633
Lola Maxi, Goldie’s back.

474
00:20:47,304 --> 00:20:48,464
How’s it going?

475
00:20:48,617 --> 00:20:50,031
About twenty more minutes!

476
00:20:50,204 --> 00:20:51,951
- Twenty minutes?!
- Yes!

477
00:20:51,963 --> 00:20:53,036
Twenty minutes, Lola Maxi?!

478
00:20:53,061 --> 00:20:54,287
Okay! Uh…

479
00:20:55,501 --> 00:20:58,961
is there anything
I can do or buy to help?

480
00:20:59,048 --> 00:21:00,548
- Yes!
- What is it?

481
00:21:00,782 --> 00:21:04,542
Keep panicking!
Because your panicking really helps me!

482
00:21:04,567 --> 00:21:05,738
Panic! Alright, here we go!

483
00:21:05,763 --> 00:21:07,532
- Okay, here I go!
- This is it, this is it!

484
00:21:11,470 --> 00:21:12,470
Ah…

485
00:21:12,788 --> 00:21:15,864
ah… here it is, Madame.

486
00:21:15,889 --> 00:21:17,013
Miss Goldie!

487
00:21:17,292 --> 00:21:19,373
And this isn’t even the
ensaymada I ordered!

488
00:21:19,451 --> 00:21:21,354
Oh, yes, Miss Goldie!

489
00:21:21,379 --> 00:21:24,587
Actually, these are some
of our specialty pastries!

490
00:21:24,612 --> 00:21:27,624
Compliments of the chef—that’s me.

491
00:21:28,105 --> 00:21:33,406
But just so you know, I graduated
culinary arts, specializing in desserts—

492
00:21:33,431 --> 00:21:34,521
I didn’t ask!

493
00:21:34,941 --> 00:21:36,801
And it’s Miss Goldie!

494
00:21:41,194 --> 00:21:44,204
Mmm, I like it!

495
00:21:44,456 --> 00:21:45,456
You really do?!

496
00:21:46,123 --> 00:21:48,516
I’d like it if I didn’t have taste buds!

497
00:21:49,911 --> 00:21:54,176
But since I do, I have to
say—you impressed me!

498
00:21:54,971 --> 00:21:57,751
W-wow! Really?

499
00:21:57,899 --> 00:22:01,752
You impressed me with
your nerve to serve me this!

500
00:22:02,025 --> 00:22:04,698
It’s like I’m eating dirt
mixed with sugar!

501
00:22:04,871 --> 00:22:05,871
Uh…

502
00:22:06,130 --> 00:22:08,989
You’re lucky this isn’t
what I came here for!

503
00:22:09,014 --> 00:22:12,211
I came for your ensaymada!

504
00:22:12,236 --> 00:22:13,236
Mmmm…

505
00:22:13,241 --> 00:22:14,241
Good thing!

506
00:22:14,853 --> 00:22:16,185
- Thank you!
- Mmm!

507
00:22:16,978 --> 00:22:17,978
Thank you!

508
00:22:18,860 --> 00:22:20,220
- Thank you!
- What time is it?

509
00:22:20,259 --> 00:22:24,215
My love, I swear, stop me already!
This woman is going too far!

510
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:26,456
- Just a little bit. Just one slap!
- Let it go!

511
00:22:26,481 --> 00:22:27,980
Let it go, my love! My
love, my love, my love.

512
00:22:28,019 --> 00:22:29,019
I’m going to confront her!

513
00:22:29,044 --> 00:22:30,044
- My love.
- What?!

514
00:22:30,069 --> 00:22:31,290
Think of what I always say, alright?

515
00:22:31,315 --> 00:22:32,315
Mm?

516
00:22:32,324 --> 00:22:34,464
Customer comes first.

517
00:22:34,489 --> 00:22:36,045
Ugh! I don’t believe in that!
Not this time!

518
00:22:36,070 --> 00:22:37,491
- Just let it go, please.
- Okay! Just let me go.

519
00:22:37,516 --> 00:22:38,599
My love! Please, just let it go!

520
00:22:38,657 --> 00:22:42,817
And so, she’s the winner of
this episode’s baking challenge!

521
00:22:43,705 --> 00:22:44,705
What do you think?

522
00:22:45,085 --> 00:22:46,085
Three things.

523
00:22:46,464 --> 00:22:47,464
First,

524
00:22:47,781 --> 00:22:50,194
the first contestant
should’ve won!

525
00:22:52,098 --> 00:22:53,098
Second,

526
00:22:53,474 --> 00:22:55,451
where’s my ensaymada?

527
00:22:55,476 --> 00:22:56,498
It’s taking forever!

528
00:22:57,280 --> 00:23:01,605
And third—dear,
you need moisturizer.

529
00:23:01,810 --> 00:23:02,930
You look haggard!

530
00:23:05,209 --> 00:23:08,219
Let me just check, okay?
I’ll check your ensaymada now, okay?

531
00:23:10,522 --> 00:23:12,732
Tash, did you manage
to entertain Miss Goldie?

532
00:23:12,756 --> 00:23:15,059
- Is everything okay?
- Dad, I tried!

533
00:23:15,279 --> 00:23:17,166
And she called me haggard!

534
00:23:18,263 --> 00:23:19,263
Tasha—

535
00:23:19,278 --> 00:23:20,285
Haggard!

536
00:23:20,875 --> 00:23:25,034
Remember what I told you—baby, baby, baby.
Like I said, the customer comes first.

537
00:23:25,109 --> 00:23:27,882
Just endure it a little longer, okay?
Hang in there!

538
00:23:29,339 --> 00:23:30,339
Fine!

539
00:23:30,401 --> 00:23:31,401
Okay?

540
00:23:39,399 --> 00:23:40,399
Lola Maxi!

541
00:23:42,067 --> 00:23:43,854
- Lola Maxi!
- What happened to you?

542
00:23:44,032 --> 00:23:45,032
What happened?

543
00:23:46,834 --> 00:23:48,854
I did everything…

544
00:23:49,351 --> 00:23:50,478
Goldie’s here…

545
00:23:50,948 --> 00:23:53,088
Oh, it’s so hard!

546
00:23:53,212 --> 00:23:54,212
So, what’s…?

547
00:23:54,430 --> 00:23:55,430
Is it done?

548
00:23:56,047 --> 00:23:57,047
Or not?

549
00:23:58,004 --> 00:24:00,788
- Of course, I finished it!
- It’s done?!

550
00:24:00,819 --> 00:24:03,991
Yes, it’s done! Quick, quick, quick!

551
00:24:04,016 --> 00:24:05,915
Oh, let’s go! Let’s go! Come on!
Lola Maxi, thank you so much—

552
00:24:13,533 --> 00:24:15,919
Thank you both so much.

553
00:24:16,072 --> 00:24:18,596
We’re exhausted.
And ugh… this part of me hurts so much!

554
00:24:18,621 --> 00:24:21,202
I had such a fun birthday.
I’m so glad you’re here.

555
00:24:21,279 --> 00:24:23,553
Oh, this sounds like it’s time to go home!

556
00:24:23,630 --> 00:24:24,630
Let’s go! Time to leave!

557
00:24:24,642 --> 00:24:25,642
- Can we go home now?
- Can we, Sir?

558
00:24:25,667 --> 00:24:26,667
No, not yet.

559
00:24:26,692 --> 00:24:30,439
Before you leave,
we’ve got one more thing to do.

560
00:24:30,696 --> 00:24:31,696
One more thing?

561
00:24:31,783 --> 00:24:32,963
Who wants to go first?

562
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:35,867
- Uh—Sir! He does!
- Yeah, him!

563
00:24:35,892 --> 00:24:38,193
He was already wishing
to die the other day—

564
00:24:38,218 --> 00:24:39,341
Hey! Wait, wait, wait!

565
00:24:39,645 --> 00:24:41,319
What are you even
talking about—dying?

566
00:24:41,414 --> 00:24:42,414
Nobody’s dying!

567
00:24:42,729 --> 00:24:45,135
We’re going to play the game…uh…

568
00:24:45,624 --> 00:24:46,624
smash the pot!

569
00:24:46,632 --> 00:24:46,963
- Oh!
- Oh, look at that!

570
00:24:46,988 --> 00:24:49,065
- I’ll go first! I’ll do it!
- Sir! I’ll go first!

571
00:24:49,090 --> 00:24:51,426
Hey! You didn’t want
to earlier! I’ll go first!

572
00:24:51,484 --> 00:24:53,650
I’ll go so we can get this over with!

573
00:24:53,864 --> 00:24:55,408
- I’ll do it!
- Alright, alright.

574
00:24:55,999 --> 00:24:57,379
I’ll go first.

575
00:24:58,082 --> 00:24:59,322
You know,

576
00:25:00,042 --> 00:25:06,682
we actually thought you were
going to kill us after all this.

577
00:25:07,501 --> 00:25:10,501
We were convinced you’re a serial killer!

578
00:25:10,913 --> 00:25:12,627
No, I’m not a serial killer.

579
00:25:13,244 --> 00:25:15,278
Like I said earlier,

580
00:25:16,152 --> 00:25:18,712
I live alone.

581
00:25:19,051 --> 00:25:21,105
We’re poor.

582
00:25:21,663 --> 00:25:24,284
Then when I finally got some money…

583
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:28,134
I could celebrate my birthday.

584
00:25:28,391 --> 00:25:29,817
It’s good you two are here to…

585
00:25:29,842 --> 00:25:32,794
Ah, so that’s why there’s food,
balloons, and even cake?

586
00:25:32,819 --> 00:25:33,819
Mm-hmm…

587
00:25:33,820 --> 00:25:35,894
Oh, so Mang Kurt’s a loner.

588
00:25:36,084 --> 00:25:37,084
Exactly.

589
00:25:37,241 --> 00:25:38,241
Mang Kurt,

590
00:25:39,006 --> 00:25:44,601
since it’s your birthday and we’re playing
smash the pot, why don’t you go first?

591
00:25:44,633 --> 00:25:47,779
Here, take this…

592
00:25:48,092 --> 00:25:50,618
I’ll put a blindfold on you…

593
00:25:50,643 --> 00:25:52,968
I haven’t done this in ages!

594
00:25:53,478 --> 00:25:55,428
- Really!
- Is he going first, Iskineport?

595
00:25:55,453 --> 00:25:57,470
Of course!
The pot is right over here, alright?

596
00:25:57,495 --> 00:25:58,711
- Yes!
- Raise the stick!

597
00:25:58,736 --> 00:25:59,736
- Alright!
- Smash it!

598
00:25:59,761 --> 00:26:00,774
- What’s happening?
- Smash it!

599
00:26:01,209 --> 00:26:02,684
- Left! Go left!
- I’m dizzy!

600
00:26:02,709 --> 00:26:06,147
Left! It’s on the right! Move to
the right! It’s on the right! Left!

601
00:26:10,412 --> 00:26:11,412
There it is!

602
00:26:12,043 --> 00:26:13,043
Finally!

603
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:14,332
- Yes!
- Finally!

604
00:26:14,357 --> 00:26:15,357
Yes!

605
00:26:15,382 --> 00:26:17,376
I said I could wait but
I didn’t think this long.

606
00:26:17,379 --> 00:26:18,619
But finally it’s here!

607
00:26:18,644 --> 00:26:20,112
Sorry about the wait, okay? Here.

608
00:26:21,251 --> 00:26:22,251
Hmm.

609
00:26:22,345 --> 00:26:23,532
It looks presentable.

610
00:26:25,519 --> 00:26:27,239
Smells fresh from the oven.

611
00:26:29,471 --> 00:26:30,471
But how does it taste?

612
00:26:48,921 --> 00:26:49,921
Water, please!

613
00:26:50,193 --> 00:26:51,194
Water? Water?

614
00:26:51,307 --> 00:26:52,608
- Ah, water!
- Andres, water! Water, water!

615
00:26:52,633 --> 00:26:54,797
- Water, water, water! Water, water!
- Water, water, water, water!

616
00:26:54,822 --> 00:26:55,822
Andres!

617
00:26:55,827 --> 00:26:57,674
Sorry, sorry! Here it is, here it is.

618
00:26:58,949 --> 00:27:01,455
Sorry, Miss Goldie! My apologies!

619
00:27:02,712 --> 00:27:04,638
You made me wait so long.

620
00:27:04,896 --> 00:27:06,116
You bored me.

621
00:27:06,867 --> 00:27:08,880
And after all that—this?!

622
00:27:09,274 --> 00:27:10,654
How dare you?!

623
00:27:10,684 --> 00:27:13,711
And for the last time,
it’s Miss Goldie!

624
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:15,873
Can you repeat it?

625
00:27:15,974 --> 00:27:19,534
Please! Say it over and over
until it sticks in your head!

626
00:27:19,559 --> 00:27:22,580
Uh… sorry… Miss Madame Goldie!

627
00:27:23,631 --> 00:27:24,837
Sorry, Miss Goldie!

628
00:27:24,862 --> 00:27:26,392
- Miss Goldie. I’m sorry.
- Say it again!

629
00:27:26,434 --> 00:27:27,874
I’m sorry, Miss Goldie!

630
00:27:27,899 --> 00:27:29,227
I’m sorry, Miss Goldie!

631
00:27:29,252 --> 00:27:30,252
Again, again!

632
00:27:30,417 --> 00:27:31,890
- I'm sorry, Miss Goldie!
- Again!

633
00:27:32,270 --> 00:27:33,917
- I'm sorry, Miss Goldie!
- Again! Repeat it!

634
00:27:34,096 --> 00:27:35,343
I'm sorry, Miss Goldie! I'm sorry!

635
00:27:35,368 --> 00:27:37,875
- Again!
- That's enough! Stop it already!

636
00:27:37,944 --> 00:27:40,157
Dad, relax!

637
00:27:40,656 --> 00:27:42,036
The customer is always right!

638
00:27:42,061 --> 00:27:44,153
No, no! Not in this situation!

639
00:27:44,632 --> 00:27:47,172
My son has apologized so many times
already, and you’re still embarrassing him?

640
00:27:47,583 --> 00:27:49,496
What if I embarrass
our whole family instead?

641
00:27:49,891 --> 00:27:53,077
What if I write a review and
shut down your business?

642
00:27:53,157 --> 00:27:54,157
That’s fine!

643
00:27:54,479 --> 00:27:58,124
Go ahead and shut down this bakery.
It’s okay, I don’t mind.

644
00:27:58,533 --> 00:28:00,640
But I won’t allow you
to humiliate my child!

645
00:28:00,790 --> 00:28:04,362
What happened was an accident, but
the way you’re speaking is just too much!

646
00:28:04,704 --> 00:28:06,810
You’re acting this way because you don’t
have a child, you don’t have a family,

647
00:28:06,835 --> 00:28:09,868
so you don’t understand
what this feels like, Miss Goldie!

648
00:28:09,955 --> 00:28:12,903
Mmm! Snap, period, end of story, girl!

649
00:28:12,928 --> 00:28:14,640
Don’t even twitch!

650
00:28:14,824 --> 00:28:16,177
- Mmm!
- Exactly!

651
00:28:16,202 --> 00:28:17,322
That’s right!

652
00:28:17,347 --> 00:28:19,584
Oh, there, there,
what do you have to say now?

653
00:28:19,609 --> 00:28:22,715
That’s right! Now leave!

654
00:28:22,772 --> 00:28:26,705
I’ll post this on social media
and make it go viral, Miss Goldie!

655
00:28:26,730 --> 00:28:29,197
Bye, Miss Goldie! Bye!

656
00:28:32,373 --> 00:28:33,373
Unbelievable!

657
00:28:34,359 --> 00:28:35,606
Good thing you backed off.

658
00:28:35,869 --> 00:28:36,869
- Exactly.
- Sorry, Dad.

659
00:28:36,894 --> 00:28:40,661
No! It’s okay. Don’t worry about it.
You don’t need to keep apologizing.

660
00:28:40,686 --> 00:28:44,344
Just one apology is enough, right?
What happened earlier was wrong, wasn’t it?

661
00:28:45,848 --> 00:28:47,572
- Thank you, really.
- Welcome, kuya!

662
00:28:47,597 --> 00:28:49,311
- Thank you, thank you!
- We got your back, Kuya!

663
00:28:49,356 --> 00:28:50,770
- Thank you so much!
- Thank you!

664
00:28:50,795 --> 00:28:53,869
No worries. Sorry if I got a bit
carried away with emotions.

665
00:28:57,854 --> 00:28:59,061
Dad, I’m sorry.

666
00:29:00,422 --> 00:29:04,369
After all the effort you’ve put in, because
of my mistake, the bakery might close.

667
00:29:05,933 --> 00:29:06,933
- Andres…
- I’m sorry, I really am.

668
00:29:07,211 --> 00:29:08,211
Andres…

669
00:29:08,648 --> 00:29:10,941
you don’t need to apologize.
What are you talking about?

670
00:29:12,562 --> 00:29:17,483
I meant it when I said it’s okay
even if the bakery closes.

671
00:29:17,577 --> 00:29:18,577
It’s true!

672
00:29:19,925 --> 00:29:22,678
You know what I can’t accept?

673
00:29:24,021 --> 00:29:26,788
When someone hurts or insults you.

674
00:29:27,068 --> 00:29:28,281
That’s not okay with me.

675
00:29:28,371 --> 00:29:31,064
It’s not okay with any parent.

676
00:29:31,089 --> 00:29:32,419
So, don’t think about it anymore, okay?

677
00:29:32,630 --> 00:29:33,630
Alright.

678
00:29:37,336 --> 00:29:38,342
It’s fine, Andres. It’s okay!

679
00:29:38,876 --> 00:29:39,876
Enough of that, big bro!

680
00:29:40,976 --> 00:29:42,643
We know what happened
to our little guy!

681
00:29:43,338 --> 00:29:44,345
He’s not at fault!

682
00:29:44,411 --> 00:29:45,857
The one at fault is the person
who disrespected you!

683
00:29:45,882 --> 00:29:47,164
- The one who yelled at you!
- Mmm!

684
00:29:47,189 --> 00:29:48,866
If you want, we’ll go to
her house and confront her!

685
00:29:48,963 --> 00:29:52,362
- Let’s go!
- Hey! Stop it, that’s not right!

686
00:29:52,461 --> 00:29:55,201
- And wait, where did you even come from?
- Yeah, really!

687
00:29:55,238 --> 00:29:59,038
Oh! Kuya, we took some time at
the place where we delivered the cake.

688
00:29:59,404 --> 00:30:01,104
We thought it was a serial killer!

689
00:30:01,129 --> 00:30:02,348
Serial kil–what?!

690
00:30:02,373 --> 00:30:03,355
Serial killer?

691
00:30:03,590 --> 00:30:05,436
You know, it’s a long story.

692
00:30:05,461 --> 00:30:09,228
I can’t explain it now,
or we’ll be here forever.

693
00:30:09,626 --> 00:30:12,859
But you know what’s important?

694
00:30:12,884 --> 00:30:14,152
What? What is it?

695
00:30:14,291 --> 00:30:20,080
I realized that people who you
think are bad are actually bad.

696
00:30:20,527 --> 00:30:21,914
Just send the message clearly.

697
00:30:22,196 --> 00:30:23,476
What’s so funny?

698
00:30:23,988 --> 00:30:25,275
It’s just that you’re trying to explain it!

699
00:30:25,300 --> 00:30:27,592
When you meet someone
and think they’re bad…

700
00:30:27,617 --> 00:30:28,617
Oh, don’t judge them!

701
00:30:28,642 --> 00:30:29,953
- Don’t judge!
- Exactly!

702
00:30:30,015 --> 00:30:31,662
Because, you see, the person
we delivered the cake to…

703
00:30:31,687 --> 00:30:33,463
- What about them?
- They gave us this…

704
00:30:33,541 --> 00:30:36,194
- A tip?!
- Wait, wait! That's a tip?!

705
00:30:36,219 --> 00:30:37,219
- Yeah!
- All of that is the tip?!

706
00:30:37,798 --> 00:30:38,811
So don’t worry!

707
00:30:38,910 --> 00:30:40,877
We’re treating you out!

708
00:30:41,074 --> 00:30:42,574
Let’s go eat noodles!

709
00:30:42,599 --> 00:30:44,389
Noodles? That sounds different!

710
00:30:44,414 --> 00:30:46,436
To change things up!
Sounds good, right?!

711
00:30:49,483 --> 00:30:50,990
- What do you think, my love?
- Yeah, sounds great!

712
00:30:51,489 --> 00:30:52,631
- Alright.
- I’m just fixing this

713
00:30:52,665 --> 00:30:53,791
to make it look nice.

714
00:30:54,575 --> 00:30:56,515
Oh, why are you here?

715
00:30:57,785 --> 00:31:00,118
I just wanted to personally
hand this to you.

716
00:31:00,960 --> 00:31:02,640
It has my article about your bakery.

717
00:31:05,465 --> 00:31:06,465
You know,

718
00:31:07,271 --> 00:31:10,691
you don’t get to decide
whether we stay open or close.

719
00:31:11,094 --> 00:31:13,494
As long as there are
customers coming in,

720
00:31:13,858 --> 00:31:15,091
we’ll stay open.

721
00:31:15,136 --> 00:31:16,407
Even if it’s just one.

722
00:31:16,837 --> 00:31:18,371
So, can you open now?

723
00:31:18,804 --> 00:31:19,870
I’m a customer, right?

724
00:31:20,792 --> 00:31:21,792
You’ll buy something?!

725
00:31:22,338 --> 00:31:23,705
Four ensaymadas, please.

726
00:31:23,806 --> 00:31:25,728
- Four ensaymadas?
- Four?! Huh?!

727
00:31:25,914 --> 00:31:28,688
Oh, okay… I’ll get them for you!
Just a moment.

728
00:31:29,998 --> 00:31:30,998
You know,

729
00:31:31,368 --> 00:31:34,934
the last time I asked for water,
it was because I choked

730
00:31:36,097 --> 00:31:38,784
—I was surprised at how delicious
your ensaymada was.

731
00:31:39,466 --> 00:31:41,612
I really liked it. It was so good.

732
00:31:41,938 --> 00:31:44,578
I also want to apologize
for yelling at your son.

733
00:31:45,135 --> 00:31:48,768
I was just shocked because, well,
your ensaymada is really that good!

734
00:31:49,279 --> 00:31:50,279
So, I’m sorry.

735
00:31:51,891 --> 00:31:53,118
Oh, alright…it’s okay, no problem.

736
00:31:53,622 --> 00:31:54,948
- Here you go.
- Alright, wrap it up, my love!

737
00:31:55,766 --> 00:31:57,330
- This is freshly made!
- Yes, freshly baked!

738
00:31:57,391 --> 00:31:59,738
Really? It’s my favorite!

739
00:32:00,129 --> 00:32:01,649
Oh, thank you!

740
00:32:01,674 --> 00:32:02,853
- Thank you so much!
- You’re welcome!

741
00:32:02,954 --> 00:32:04,941
You know, we’d like to
give this to you for free,

742
00:32:04,965 --> 00:32:06,221
but we’ll take your payment.

743
00:32:06,398 --> 00:32:07,398
- Yes.
- We need it too.

744
00:32:07,441 --> 00:32:08,903
- Thank you so much!
- You’re welcome!

745
00:32:08,983 --> 00:32:10,250
- Thank you!
- Thank you so much, Miss Goldie!

746
00:32:10,275 --> 00:32:11,275
Keep the change!

747
00:32:11,387 --> 00:32:12,400
Miss Goldie, thank you!

748
00:32:12,425 --> 00:32:13,673
Thank you, Miss Goldie!

749
00:32:13,698 --> 00:32:15,031
- Hey, keep the change!
- Keep the change!

750
00:32:15,677 --> 00:32:17,504
- Did you hear what she said?!
- Yummy!

751
00:32:20,338 --> 00:32:21,338
Yummy?

752
00:32:22,731 --> 00:32:23,824
Hey!

753
00:32:25,588 --> 00:32:27,547
The article is out!

754
00:32:27,925 --> 00:32:30,066
Wow, BFF! Condolences

755
00:32:30,844 --> 00:32:32,170
I know it’s sad, right?

756
00:32:32,470 --> 00:32:33,536
Your bakery might close.

757
00:32:34,021 --> 00:32:36,167
You might even separate.

758
00:32:36,622 --> 00:32:38,262
That could happen,

759
00:32:38,953 --> 00:32:41,013
especially with such a big problem.

760
00:32:41,568 --> 00:32:42,568
Right, that.

761
00:32:42,967 --> 00:32:45,061
BFF, it really is a huge problem.

762
00:32:45,235 --> 00:32:52,562
We don’t know how we’ll handle
the flood of hundreds, thousands,

763
00:32:52,622 --> 00:32:57,328
thousands, even millions of
customers coming to our bake shop!

764
00:32:57,593 --> 00:32:59,786
- Exactly! Congrats, my love!
- Right?!

765
00:32:59,848 --> 00:33:01,515
I’m so happy!

766
00:33:01,688 --> 00:33:03,141
- What congratulations?!
- Mm-mm!

767
00:33:03,166 --> 00:33:05,495
What are you even saying
congratulations for?! Wait a second!

768
00:33:05,931 --> 00:33:06,931
Read it!

769
00:33:09,747 --> 00:33:10,747
Where is it?

770
00:33:13,868 --> 00:33:21,250
“Bake Haus of U Ensaymada.
The Best in the Metro!” ?!

771
00:33:21,331 --> 00:33:23,077
- Yeah!
- This can’t be!

772
00:33:23,317 --> 00:33:24,317
How did this happen?!

773
00:33:24,342 --> 00:33:26,114
- Did you rig this?!
- Huh?!

774
00:33:26,139 --> 00:33:27,551
Did you bribe them?! This can’t be!

775
00:33:27,576 --> 00:33:28,629
Huh? Huh? Oh no!

776
00:33:29,779 --> 00:33:31,239
I’ll ruin your bakery!

777
00:33:31,264 --> 00:33:33,561
You tricked me again!
What did you do?!

778
00:33:33,586 --> 00:33:35,956
- Tso K! Chef K! Chef K!
- What did you do?!

779
00:33:35,981 --> 00:33:38,050
- Don’t, don’t!
- You tricked me!

780
00:33:38,122 --> 00:33:40,469
The taste itself is delicious!”

781
00:33:41,003 --> 00:33:43,235
Wow!
“But their secret ingredient?

782
00:33:43,735 --> 00:33:44,735
Love.

783
00:33:44,903 --> 00:33:48,460
And this family-owned
business has lots of it to give.

784
00:33:49,077 --> 00:33:54,512
That’s why Bake Haus of
U’s ensaymada is the best.

785
00:33:54,765 --> 00:33:56,165
U should try it.”

786
00:33:56,311 --> 00:33:57,311
Oh…wow!

787
00:33:59,093 --> 00:34:00,226
Amazing!

788
00:34:01,132 --> 00:34:05,326
Wow, we really overcame
such a big challenge, huh?

789
00:34:05,354 --> 00:34:06,354
Hey!

790
00:34:06,379 --> 00:34:09,298
Go, go, go!
There’s someone at the door, Dad!

791
00:34:10,507 --> 00:34:12,167
Aren’t you the one closer to the door?

792
00:34:12,495 --> 00:34:13,802
Why are you pushing me?

793
00:34:16,419 --> 00:34:17,809
- Hey!
- Hello!

794
00:34:17,834 --> 00:34:19,686
Miss Goldie! Hey, come in! Come in!

795
00:34:20,186 --> 00:34:22,419
We were just talking about you!

796
00:34:22,550 --> 00:34:24,525
- Sit down, sit down!
- Thank you, Miss Goldie!

797
00:34:24,550 --> 00:34:25,550
Have a seat, have a seat!

798
00:34:25,646 --> 00:34:30,038
You know, I’m so excited to rewrite
your article about your reopening!

799
00:34:30,256 --> 00:34:31,894
- Congratulations!
- Oh, thank you, thank you!

800
00:34:32,038 --> 00:34:33,038
And did you know,

801
00:34:33,246 --> 00:34:35,192
it’s now Mrs. Goldie!

802
00:34:35,217 --> 00:34:36,237
- Oh!
- Yes!

803
00:34:36,262 --> 00:34:37,262
- Mrs. Goldie?!
- Mrs. Goldie?!

804
00:34:38,118 --> 00:34:41,291
You know, my husband and
I have so much in common…

805
00:34:41,648 --> 00:34:43,881
like at first, we were both grumpy,

806
00:34:44,138 --> 00:34:45,785
but not really, right?

807
00:34:46,133 --> 00:34:49,893
And actually, he’s a client here;
he always orders from you!

808
00:34:49,918 --> 00:34:50,950
- Client?
- Yes!

809
00:34:50,975 --> 00:34:52,616
- From us?
- I’m sure you know him!

810
00:34:53,020 --> 00:34:54,946
Darling! Honey!

811
00:34:54,971 --> 00:34:56,248
- Hello! Hi!
- Hi!

812
00:34:56,581 --> 00:34:57,861
- Have a seat!
- Hello!

813
00:34:57,885 --> 00:34:58,885
This is my…

814
00:34:59,154 --> 00:35:00,667
Hi guys! Wassup, wassup!

815
00:35:00,907 --> 00:35:02,535
- Chard!
- This is my husband!

816
00:35:02,572 --> 00:35:03,967
And, this is my wife.

817
00:35:04,079 --> 00:35:05,238
So, we are called –

818
00:35:05,491 --> 00:35:06,824
Husband and wife.

819
00:35:07,930 --> 00:35:09,478
Oh, hold on! I’m so surprised!

820
00:35:09,993 --> 00:35:11,358
When did you get married?

821
00:35:11,472 --> 00:35:13,941
We got married yesterday,
early in the morning,

822
00:35:13,965 --> 00:35:17,091
about 3:32 and seven seconds.

823
00:35:17,123 --> 00:35:23,678
It was officiated by
Father Sebastian Morrison,

824
00:35:23,702 --> 00:35:26,166
the greatest father of them all.

825
00:35:26,191 --> 00:35:28,727
Your husband isn’t very talkative, huh?

826
00:35:28,752 --> 00:35:29,963
- Ah, yes!
- And she was…

827
00:35:30,422 --> 00:35:31,760
She was…yes…

828
00:35:32,855 --> 00:35:34,450
- Congratulations!
- Let’s eat first.

829
00:35:34,475 --> 00:35:35,776
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations!

830
00:35:37,864 --> 00:35:39,849
Anyway, guys, the intro!

831
00:35:39,874 --> 00:35:40,990
- Ah, yes!
- Wait a second, okay?

832
00:35:41,015 --> 00:35:41,662
We just need to excuse
ourselves for a moment.

833
00:35:41,687 --> 00:35:43,631
Let’s say goodbye!

834
00:35:44,229 --> 00:35:45,372
- Okay!
- Alright!

835
00:35:45,473 --> 00:35:46,970
One, two, three!

836
00:35:47,835 --> 00:35:49,517
In struggle and in joy,

837
00:35:49,815 --> 00:35:53,594
Pers is first, Pers is the hero!
